ACCESS_LEVEL_ROOT

public static final java.lang.String ACCESS_LEVEL_ROOT
Available only in Google Apps domains. User is a domain administrator, and therefore has full owner access to the calendar regardless of access control settings.

Constant Field Values

category

public Category category
Category tag in Calendar feed

accessLevel

public Value accessLevel
Indicates what level of access the current user (the one whose credentials are being used to request the metafeed) has to the calendar. Possible values are ACCESS_LEVEL_EDITOR, ACCESS_LEVEL_FREEBUSY, ACCESS_LEVEL_NONE, ACCESS_LEVEL_OWNER, ACCESS_LEVEL_READ and ACCESS_LEVEL_ROOT.

color

public Value color
The color used to highlight a calendar in the user's browser. Must be one of the hexadecimal RGB color values listed here.
